'''''Halls of Montezuma: A Battle History of the U.S. Marine Corps''''' is a [[strategy video game]] developed by [[Strategic Studies Group]] in 1987 for the [[Apple II series|Apple II]]. Ports were later released for the [[Commodore 64]], [[Amiga]], [[DOS]], and [[Apple IIGS]].

==Gameplay==
''Halls of Montezuma'' is a war simulation game that includes all major battles in which the [[United States Marine Corps]] were involved.<ref name=":0">{{Cite magazine |last=Lesser |first=Hartley |last2=Lesser |first2=Patricia |last3=Lesser |first3=Kirk |date=April 1988 |title=Halls of Montezuma: A Battle History of the U.S. Marine Corps |url=https://annarchive.com/files/Drmg132.pdf#page=86 |magazine=[[Dragon (magazine)|Dragon]] |page=84}}</ref>

==Reception==
In 1988, ''[[Dragon (magazine)|Dragon]]'' gave the game 4 out of 5 stars.<ref name=":0" /> Johnny L. Wilson reviewed the game for ''[[Computer Gaming World]]'', and stated that "HOM does not allow players to be the 'god of the battlefield,' but it sure offers an Olympian challenge."<ref name="CGW45">{{cite magazine |last=Wilson |first=Johnny L. |date=March 1988 |title=A Proud Tradition: Strategic Studies Group's "Halls of Montezuma" |url=https://archive.org/details/Computer_Gaming_World_Issue_45/page/n23/mode/2up |magazine=Computer Gaming World |volume=1 |issue=45 |pages=24–25, 46 |via=[[Internet Archive]]}}</ref>

In a 1990 survey of wargames ''[[Computer Gaming World]]'' gave the game three-plus stars out of five,<ref name="brooks199010">{{cite news |last=Brooks |first=M. Evan |date=October 1990 |title=Computer Strategy and Wargames: Pre-20th Century |pages=13 |magazine=[[Computer Gaming World]] |url=https://www.cgwmuseum.org/galleries/issues/cgw_75.pdf#page=13 |access-date=16 November 2013}}</ref> in 1991 three stars,<ref name=":1">{{Cite magazine |last=Brooks |first=M. Evan |date=November 1991 |title=Computer Strategy and Wargames: The 1900-1950 Epoch |url=https://www.cgwmuseum.org/galleries/issues/cgw_88.pdf#page=145 |magazine=[[Computer Gaming World]] |issue=88 |page=145 |access-date=6 May 2023}}</ref> in 1993 three stars,<ref name="brooks199308">{{cite news |author=Brooks |first=M. Evan |date=August 1993 |title=Wargame Survey Version 2.0 |pages=128 |magazine=[[Computer Gaming World]] |url=https://www.cgwmuseum.org/galleries/issues/cgw_109.pdf#page=128 |access-date=12 July 2014}}</ref><ref name="brooks199309">{{cite news |author=Brooks |first=M. Evan |date=September 1993 |title=Brooks' Book of Wargames: 1900-1950, A-P |page=118 |magazine=[[Computer Gaming World]] |url=https://www.cgwmuseum.org/galleries/issues/cgw_110.pdf#page=118 |access-date=30 July 2014}}</ref> and in 1994 two-plus stars.<ref name="brooks199401">{{Cite magazine |last=Brooks |first=M. Evan |date=January 1994 |title=War In Our Time: A Survey Of Wargames From 1950-2000 |url=https://www.cgwmuseum.org/galleries/issues/cgw_114.pdf |magazine=[[Computer Gaming World]] |pages=194–212}}</ref>

